<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold;">Installed Python Versions</span></div><div>=&gt; <span style="font-weight: bold;"> ls</span> <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">/usr/local/bin</span> | <span style="font-weight: bold;">grep</span> <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">python</span></div><div>p<span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">ython</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">python2</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">python2-config</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">python2.7</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">python2.7-config</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">python3</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">python3.6</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">python3.6-config</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">python3.6m</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">python3.6m-config</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);">/usr/local/bin/python -&gt; /usr/local/bin/python2.7</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);">/usr/local/bin/python2 -&gt; python2.7</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);">/usr/local/bin/python2-config -&gt; python2.7-config</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);">/usr/local/bin/python2.7</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);">/usr/local/bin/python2.7-config</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">/usr/local/bin/python3 -&gt; <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">/usr/local/bin/python3.6</span></span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">/usr/local/bin/python3.6</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">/usr/local/bin/python3.6-config -&gt; python3.6m-config</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">/usr/local/bin/python3.6m</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">/usr/local/bin/python3.6m-config</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold;">PIP Installation</span></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div>Download the “<span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">get-pip.py</span>” from here: <a href="https://pip.readthedocs.io/en/stable/installing/">https://pip.readthedocs.io/en/stable/installing/</a></div><div>=&gt; wget https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Python 2.7 </span></div><div>=&gt; <span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);">sudo</span> <span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);">python2</span> <span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">get-pip.py</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># This will install the PIP under /usr/local/bin</span></div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> which</span> <span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">pip2   </span></div><div>      <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);"> </span><span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">/usr/local/bin</span>/<span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">pip2</span></div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> pip2  --version</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">    </span><span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">pip 9.0.1 </span>from<span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);"> </span><span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);">/usr/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages (python 2.7) </span><span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);"> </span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Python 3.6</span></div><div>=&gt; <span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);">sudo</span> <span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);">python3.6</span> <span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">get-pip.py</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">=&gt; sudo python3 get-pip.py  ( works too )</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># This will install the PIP under /usr/local/bin</span></div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> which</span> <span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">pip3</span></div><div>      <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);"> </span><span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">/usr/local/bin</span>/<span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">pip3</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Note:</span> The installation will create  <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">/usr/local/bin</span>/<span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">pip</span> to whatever version you install last.</div><div>          In my case, I’ve installed the <span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">pip3</span> last so </div><div>           <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">/usr/local/bin</span>/<span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">pip  </span>is the same file as<span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);"> </span><span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);"> </span><span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">/usr/local/bin</span><span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">/</span><span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">pip3</span>, but it not a symbolic link.</div><div>           Any way, I deleted the   <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">/usr/local/bin</span>/<span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">pip  </span>not to confuse my self.</div><div>=&gt;<span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);"> sudo</span> <span style="font-weight: bold;">rm -rf </span><span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);"> /usr/local/bin</span>/<span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">pip</span></div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> pip3 --version</span></div><div>     <span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);">pip 9.0.1</span> from <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">/usr/local/lib/python3.6/site-packages (python 3.6)</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24px;">Using the PIP as a User ( not admin)</span></div><div><br /></div><div># Note: Users who can’t use “sudo” , always must use the version of “pip” located</div><div># under ~/.local/bin.</div><div># The option “<span style="font-weight: bold;">--user</span>” lets you do that!</div><div># You can also upgradee your version of PIP :</div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;">pip</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 143, 0);"> install</span> <span style="font-weight: bold;">--user</span> <span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147);">--upgrade</span> <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">pip</span></div><div><br /></div><div># If you want to install PIP packages as a user, you need to give “--user” option: </div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> pip</span> <span style="color: rgb(0, 84, 147);">install</span><span style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 84, 147);"> </span><span style="font-weight: bold;">--user</span> <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">&lt;pakage name&gt;</span></div><div># This will install the packages under "~/.local” folder</div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div></en-note>